abla}$ , where here $d_{
abla}: \Omega^1(M,TM) 	o \Omega^2(M,TM)$ is the covariant exterior derivative associated with the Levi-Civita connection $
abla$ , and $\delta_{
abla}$ is its adjoint. Is there some kind of Weitzenböck formula connecting these two Laplacians? something like $\Delta_H-\Delta_B=C(R^{
abla})$ , where $R^{
abla}$ is the curvature tensor of $
abla$ ? I know that for real-valued one-forms, the classical Weitzenböck formula is $\Delta_H-\Delta_B=	ext{Ric}$ , where " $	ext{Ric}$ " denotes the Ricci curvature of the manifold. Can we do something similar here?

